    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of Oct 15 article on televised political advertising: two out of every three campaign dollars at all levels is spent on TV ads</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Because of an editing error, a word is omitted from an article on Page 29 of Arts &amp; Leisure today about televised political advertising. The affected sentence should read, ''The power of televised political advertising has been proved repeatedly over the last half century, to the point that two out of every three campaign dollars at all levels, or about $1 billion this year, is spent on TV ads.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Because of an editing error, a word is omitted from an article on Page 29 of Arts &amp; Leisure today about televised political advertising. The affected sentence should read, ''The power of televised political advertising has been proved repeatedly over the last half century, to the point that two out of every three campaign dollars at all levels, or about $1 billion this year, is spent on TV ads.''</p>
      </block>
